The paper deals with regular languages and their state complexity, which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). The study of state complexity also involves the use of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms for manipulating regular languages, which could be relevant to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves mathematical proofs and analysis, which could be relevant to the categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and information theory (cs.IT).
